#. type: Title #
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "`Required` - verifying that a value is provided"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
msgid "Use the `Required` rule to ensure that a value is provided (not empty)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
msgid "By default, a value is considered empty only when it is either:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
msgid "Not passed at all."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
msgid "`null`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
msgid "An empty string (after trimming)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
msgid "An empty iterable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Customizing empty condition"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
msgid ""
"Which values are considered empty can be customized via the "
"`$emptyCondition` option. Unlike in [skipOnEmpty], no normalization is "
"performed here, so only a callable or a special class is accepted. For more "
"details see the [Empty condition basics] section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
msgid ""
"An example with custom empty condition that limits empty values to `null` "
"only:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Required;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\EmptyCondition\\WhenNull;\n"
"\n"
"new Required(emptyCondition: new WhenNull());\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
msgid ""
"It's also possible to set it globally for all rules of this type at the "
"handler level via `RequiredHandler::$defaultEmptyCondition`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Usage with other rules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
msgid ""
"`Required` is rarely used by itself. When combining it with other rules, "
"make sure it's placed first:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Length;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Required;\n"
"\n"
"$rules = [\n"
"    new Required(),\n"
"    new Length(min: 1, max: 50),\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
msgid ""
"With these settings, `Length` will still run in the case of an empty value. "
"To prevent this, set up a conditional validation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Length;\n"
"use Yiisoft\\Validator\\Rule\\Required;\n"
"\n"
"$rules = [\n"
"    new Required(),\n"
"    new Length(min: 1, max: 50, skipOnError: true),\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/en/built-in-rules-required.md
msgid ""
"Other ways of configuring conditional validation are described in the "
"[Conditional validation] section."
msgstr ""

